@node "Intro" "Introduction & Usage"

     @{b}Introduction to AppReset@{ub}

     AppReset is a little AppIcon which sits on your
     Workbench,waiting for you to double-click it.

     It then asks you if you want to reset,quit AppReset,
     or cancel the request.That's it :)

     You can change the icon to suit yourself,and also
     the tooltypes :

     @{b}Tooltypes@{ub}

     DONOTWAIT - @{i}leave this alone @{ui}if you're starting it
                 from WBStartup.

     TEXT      - The text you want to appear under the
                 appicon.Don't put it in quotes,unless you
                 want them of course!

     DELAY     - Although AppReset only uses a tiny amount of
                 CPU time,you can lessen it a little by 
                 increasing the delay (in 1/50ths of a second),
                 the expense being that it takes slightly
                 longer to respond to a double-click.

     @{b}That's it.@{ub}

     Oh,appicons appear wherever they feel like,so you can't
     really specifiy a position.As far as I know,anyway.You
     soon get used to it ;)
@endnode

